EvaluatedAnnotations.Name: percentage measurement range start value
EvaluatedAnnotations.Definition: The measurement range for humidity is the range of those values of the measurement variable that is demanded to ensure that the measurement deviations of a measurement installation remain within the determined limits. The measurement range is defined by the start and end value. Setting ranges can be given for the measurement range start value and the measurement range end value. The measurement range start value is frequently given as a percentage of the measurement range end value or formed as a quotient of the measurement range end value and start value or as a percentage of the measurement voltage. Depending on the measurement installation, the following information is recommended. In addition to the measurement range, a measurement span can be given. This is the difference between the measurement range end value and the measurement range start value
